semantic_equivalence_artifact.original_latex_theorem:
[Soundness]\label{soundness i.e. initiality}
For every model $(\mathcal{C},\tp,-.-,P)$ of $\textnormal{ETT}$, there is unique a morphism $\mathbf{eTT}\to(\mathcal{C},\tp,-.-,P)$ of $\textnormal{ETT}$.

Analogously, for every model $(\mathcal{C},\tp,-.-,P)$ of $\textnormal{PTT}$, there is unique a morphism: $$\mathbf{pTT}\to(\mathcal{C},\tp,-.-,P)$$ of $\textnormal{PTT}$ and, for every model $(\mathcal{C},\tp,-.-,P)$ of $\textnormal{hPTT}$, there is unique a morphism: $$\textnormal{\texttt{h}}\mathbf{pTT}\to(\mathcal{C},\tp,-.-,P)$$ of $\textnormal{hPTT}$.

