\label{lemma x}
Let $\gamma:\Gamma$, $\delta:\Delta$ and $\omega:\Omega$ be contexts, let $(\textnormal{\texttt{f}};\textnormal{\texttt{g}})$ be a canonical context homotopy equivalence between $\gamma$ and $\delta$ and let $(\textnormal{\texttt{f}}',\textnormal{\texttt{g}}')$ be a context homotopy equivalence between $\delta$ and $\omega$.

If we are given judgements $\boldsymbol{\lfloor}\gamma\boldsymbol{\rfloor}\;S(\gamma):\textsc{Type}$, $\boldsymbol{\lfloor}\delta\boldsymbol{\rfloor}\;T(\delta):\textsc{Type}$ and $\boldsymbol{\lfloor}\omega\boldsymbol{\rfloor}\;U(\omega):\textsc{Type}$ and canonical homotopy equivalences $\langle\;\phi\;|\;\psi\;\rangle$ between $S(\gamma)$ and $T(\delta)$ relative to $(\textnormal{\texttt{f}};\textnormal{\texttt{g}})$ and $\langle\;\phi'\;|\;\psi'\;\rangle$ between $T(\delta)$ and $U(\omega)$ relative to $(\textnormal{\texttt{f}}';\textnormal{\texttt{g}}')$, then there exists a canonical homotopy equivalence $\langle\;{\phi}''\;|\;{\psi}''\;\rangle$ between $S(\gamma)$ and $U(\omega)$ relative to $(\textnormal{\texttt{f}}'\textnormal{\texttt{f}};\textnormal{\texttt{g}}\textnormal{\texttt{g}}')$ and such that: \begin{center} $\boldsymbol{\lfloor}\gamma,s:S(\gamma)\boldsymbol{\rfloor}\;{\phi}''(\gamma,s)=\phi'(\textnormal{\texttt{f}}(\gamma),\phi(\gamma,s))$\\ and equivalently $\boldsymbol{\lfloor}\gamma,u'':U(\textnormal{\texttt{f}}'(\textnormal{\texttt{f}}(\gamma)))\boldsymbol{\rfloor}\;{\psi}''(\gamma,u'')=\psi(\gamma,\psi'(\textnormal{\texttt{f}}(\gamma),u''))$. \end{center}

